-- ABU Zaria (Ahmadu Bello University)
-- ============================================================
('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Construction Law', 'The Standard Form of Building Contract (SFBC) used in Nigeria is based on:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"FIDIC conditions"},{"label":"B","text":"JCT conditions adapted for Nigerian practice"},{"label":"C","text":"NEC conditions"},{"label":"D","text":"ICC conditions"}]', 'B', 'The Nigerian SFBC is based on JCT (Joint Contracts Tribunal) conditions adapted for Nigerian construction practice. It includes provisions suited to local conditions, regulations, and professional practice.', 'medium', 2020, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 305', ARRAY['law','sfbc','jct','nigeria','abu']),

('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Construction Law', 'A contract is said to be void when:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"One party fails to perform their obligations"},{"label":"B","text":"It has no legal effect from the beginning (ab initio)"},{"label":"C","text":"It is terminated by mutual agreement"},{"label":"D","text":"The price is too low"}]', 'B', 'A void contract has no legal effect from the beginning (ab initio). It is as if the contract never existed. This differs from a voidable contract, which is valid until set aside by one of the parties.', 'medium', 2021, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 305', ARRAY['law','void','contract','legal']),

('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Contract Administration', 'The Certificate of Practical Completion in JCT contracts is issued when:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"All defects are rectified"},{"label":"B","text":"The works are complete except for minor defects that do not prevent occupation"},{"label":"C","text":"The final account is agreed"},{"label":"D","text":"The defects liability period expires"}]', 'B', 'The Certificate of Practical Completion is issued when the works are sufficiently complete for the employer to take possession, except for minor defects (patent defects) that do not prevent the use or occupation of the works.', 'medium', 2020, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 403', ARRAY['completion','certificate','jct','administration']),

('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Construction Law', 'Frustration of contract occurs when:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"One party finds the contract unprofitable"},{"label":"B","text":"An unforeseen event makes performance impossible or radically different"},{"label":"C","text":"The contractor is delayed by weather"},{"label":"D","text":"The employer changes the design"}]', 'B', 'Frustration occurs when an unforeseen event makes performance of the contract impossible, illegal, or radically different from what was originally contemplated. It automatically discharges the contract.', 'hard', 2022, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 305', ARRAY['law','frustration','contract','legal']),

('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Contract Administration', 'The Defects Liability Period (DLP) in Nigerian construction contracts is typically:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"6 months"},{"label":"B","text":"12 months"},{"label":"C","text":"18 months"},{"label":"D","text":"24 months"}]', 'B', 'The Defects Liability Period in Nigerian construction contracts is typically 12 months from the date of practical completion. During this period, the contractor is obligated to rectify any defects that appear.', 'easy', 2021, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 403', ARRAY['dlp','defects','period','contract']),

('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Contract Administration', 'An Architect''s Instruction (AI) under JCT contracts can:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"Only request minor changes to the design"},{"label":"B","text":"Order variations, changes in design, or corrections to defective work"},{"label":"C","text":"Only approve materials"},{"label":"D","text":"Only issue payment certificates"}]', 'B', 'Under JCT contracts, an Architect''s Instruction can order variations to the works, changes in design or specification, corrections to defective work, and other matters necessary for the proper execution of the works.', 'medium', 2020, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 403', ARRAY['ai','architect','instruction','jct']),

('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Construction Law', 'The distinction between a penalty and liquidated damages in construction contracts is that:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"There is no distinction"},{"label":"B","text":"Liquidated damages represent a genuine pre-estimate of loss, while penalties are惩罚性的"},{"label":"C","text":"Penalties are always enforceable"},{"label":"D","text":"Liquidated damages can never be enforced"}]', 'B', 'The legal distinction is that liquidated damages represent a genuine pre-estimate of the employer''s likely loss from delay, while penalties are惩罚性的 sums intended to punish the contractor. Courts enforce liquidated damages but not penalties.', 'hard', 2022, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 305', ARRAY['law','penalty','liquidated_damages','legal']),

('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Contract Administration', 'Variation orders in construction contracts are issued to:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"Reduce the contractor''s profit"},{"label":"B","text":"Make changes to the scope, quality, or quantity of work as required"},{"label":"C","text":"Terminate the contract"},{"label":"D","text":"Delay the project completion"}]', 'B', 'Variation orders are issued to make changes to the scope, quality, or quantity of work as required during the course of the project. They can be initiated by the employer, architect, or contractor and must be properly documented.', 'easy', 2021, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 403', ARRAY['variation','order','change','contract']),

('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Construction Law', 'The remedy of specific performance in construction law means:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"The court orders payment of damages"},{"label":"B","text":"The court orders the party to perform their contractual obligations"},{"label":"C","text":"The contract is automatically terminated"},{"label":"D","text":"The parties must negotiate a settlement"}]', 'B', 'Specific performance is an equitable remedy where the court orders a party to perform their specific contractual obligations. It is typically used when damages would be inadequate, such as for unique or specialized construction works.', 'hard', 2022, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 305', ARRAY['law','specific_performance','remedy','legal']),

('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Contract Administration', 'The purpose of a pre-tender meeting is to:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"Award the contract to the preferred bidder"},{"label":"B","text":"Clarify tender requirements and allow bidders to ask questions before submitting tenders"},{"label":"C","text":"Negotiate the contract price"},{"label":"D","text":"Sign the contract with the successful bidder"}]', 'B', 'A pre-tender meeting allows potential tenderers to seek clarification on the tender documents, site conditions, and contract requirements before submitting their tenders. This helps ensure all tenderers have a clear understanding.', 'easy', 2020, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 403', ARRAY['tender','meeting','procurement','clarification']),

('university', 'ABU Zaria Past Questions', 'Contract Administration', 'The defects notification period in NEC contracts serves a similar purpose to:', 'mcq', '[{"label":"A","text":"The defects liability period in JCT contracts"},{"label":"B","text":"The retention period in FIDIC contracts"},{"label":"C","text":"The defects notification period in JCT contracts"},{"label":"D","text":"The defects liability period in FIDIC contracts"}]', 'A', 'The defects notification period in NEC contracts serves a similar purpose to the defects liability period in JCT contracts. Both provide a period after practical completion during which the contractor must remedy defects.', 'medium', 2021, 'Ahmadu Bello University', 'QSA 403', ARRAY['nec','jct','defects','comparison']);

